Unilever Pakistan Ltd. (ULEVER) , the nationâ€™s
biggest consumer goods maker, said second-quarter profit rose
4.6 percent on higher ice cream sales.  Net income climbed to 633 million rupees ($7.3 million), or
47.61 rupees a share, in the three months ended June 30, from
605 million rupees or 45.64 rupees a share, according to a
statement today. Ice cream sales increased 20 percent.  Total sales rose to 12.6 billion rupees from 11.2 billion
rupees. The company also plans to pay a cash dividend of 105
